      "uid": "sn22.43",
      "root_name": "Attadīpasutta",
      "translated_name": null,
      "acronym": "SN 22.43",
      "blurb": "Dwell with yourself as an island and refuge, with the Dhamma as an island and refuge. How? By investigating how suffering arises from identification with the aggregates.",
      "node_type": "leaf",
      "root_lang_iso": "pli",
      "root_lang_name": "Pāli",
      "child_range": null,
      "yellow_brick_road": true,
      "yellow_brick_road_count": 3
    },
    {
      "uid": "sn22.44",
      "root_name": "Paṭipadāsutta",
      "translated_name": null,
      "acronym": "SN 22.44",
      "blurb": "Contemplation of the five aggregates as not-self is the path to the end of identity.",
      "node_type": "leaf",
      "root_lang_iso": "pli",
      "root_lang_name": "Pāli",
      "child_range": null,
      "yellow_brick_road": true,
      "yellow_brick_road_count": 3
    },
    {
      "uid": "sn22.45",
      "root_name": "Aniccasutta",
      "translated_name": null,
      "acronym": "SN 22.45",
      "blurb": "Seeing the five aggregates as impermanent, etc., leads to freedom.",
      "node_type": "leaf",
      "root_lang_iso": "pli",
      "root_lang_name": "Pāli",
      "child_range": null,
      "yellow_brick_road": true,
